Wait 24 hours and check the build report
http://bioconductor.org/checkResults/

The updated versions will not show up in today's build report as they were pushed to git too late but should appear in tomorrow's build report.
Any changes before 4:45 PM EST  will not be included in the nightly build and will be in the following days report.

If you do not want to wait that long  - You can always try cloning your package down directly from git.bioconductor.org into a new temporary directory and checking the versions.
git clone git at git.bioconductor.org:packages/DeMixT.git


For What Its Worth -  I do see the version changes in both release and devel.

Cheers,


